org.openimaj.twitter

Interface RDFAnalysisProvider


  • public interface RDFAnalysisProvider
    The analysis held in GeneralJSON can be translated to JSON very easily The same analysis cannot be easily translated to RDF so this class must be registered in GeneralJSONRDF's map to do so.

    What this means that if things add analysis to a GeneralJSONRDF instance or a USMFStatus that will eventually feed a GeneralJSONRDF instance, they should register with GeneralJSONRDF.registerRDFAnalysisProvider(String, RDFAnalysisProvider) want to

    Author:
    Sina Samangooei (ss@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

    • Method Detail

      • addAnalysis

        void addAnalysis(com.hp.hpl.jena.rdf.model.Model m,
               com.hp.hpl.jena.rdf.model.Resource analysis,
               GeneralJSON analysisSource)
        When given this analysis, fill the model with triples representing its existence. The IRI of the status the analysis is against is also provided and must be added to the model with the IRI of the analysis also.
        Parameters:
        m - the model to add triples to
        analysis - the status to associate the analysis to
        analysisSource - the analysis to transform to triples

        void init()
        Prepare yourself. Called once at the beggining of a write of a batch.
